verbose_text: Although feeding induced acute clock gene expression in peripheral tissues can be thought to result in 2 or 3 peaks of the PER2 : : LUC rhythm in response to insulin secretion after each session of food intake XREF_BIBR XREF_BIBR XREF_BIBR, the results from our study suggest that convergence of these signals would be adjusted to only 1 peak phase with a 24-h rhythm against multiple feeding conditions.
